The paper deals with distributed optimization algorithms for federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the block-cyclic structure of data in federated learning, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the CIFAR-10 dataset, which is a popular dataset in computer vision, suggesting that it could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper deals with data characteristics and biases, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
